Digital Forensics Basics

Order of Volatility (collect in this order)
1. CPU registers & cache
2. RAM (memory)
3. Network connections
4. Running processes
5. Disk / storage
6. Backup / archival media

Key Artifacts
- Windows: Event Logs, Registry, Prefetch, Browser History
- Linux: /var/log/, .bash_history, /tmp/

---
Threat Intelligence

| Type | Description | Example |

| Strategic | High-level business risk | Nation-state threat reports |
| Tactical | TTPs — how attackers operate | MITRE ATT&CK |
| Operational | Specific active campaigns | IOCs from recent breach |
| Technical | Raw indicators | IP, hash, domain |

MITRE ATT&CK Framework
- Tactics — The WHY (e.g., Initial Access, Lateral Movement)
- Techniques — The HOW (e.g., Phishing, Pass-the-Hash)
- Procedures — Specific implementation

---
IOCs (Indicators of Compromise)
- Malicious IPs / domains
- File hashes (MD5, SHA256)
- Registry keys
- Unusual outbound connections
- Anomalous user behavior
